quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  29,31,"And when Our messengers came to <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Though pronounced in Arabic as <i>Ibrahim</i>, Hisham and Ibn Zekwan in one of his narrations read it as: “Abraham”.</span>
  29,32,"He said, “Yet Lot is in it.” They said, “We know better of who is in it; <span class=""h"">we will most surely</span><span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Hamza, Al-Kesa’i, Ya’qub and Khalaf read it as: “…we will most surely save him…”</span>
  29,33,"Then, when Our messengers came to Lot, he was troubled and distressed on their account. But they said, “Do not fear nor grieve; we will <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Nafie’, Abu Amr, Ibn Amer, Hafs and Abu Ja’far read it as: “…we will save you and…”</span>
  29,34,"Indeed, <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Amer read it as: “Indeed, We will send from on high upon the people of this town…”</span>
  29,35,"And We left behind something of it as an evident sign for people who reason."
  29,36,"And to Midian<i class=""s"">(We sent) </i>their brother Shuʻaib. So he said, “O my people, worship Allah and expect the Last Day, and do not go wickedly about the land, corrupting it.”"
  29,37,"But they disbelieved him, so the Tremor overtook them and they became lifeless bodies in their home."
  29,38,"And ʻĀd{1}and Thamûd{2}as well, as it has become evident for you<a class="sup"><sup>pl </sup></a>from their<i class="s">(ruined) </i>residences. And Satan adorned their deeds for them, barring them from the way, even though they could see.",footnotes:1:The pagan tribe of Prophet Hûd.,footnotes:2:The pagan tribe of Prophet Salih.
